; Tests that flag order doesn't affect validation
; Expected warning: JVMS-001 (interface with final/super/enum/module)
; This proves:
;   1. Parser correctly handles flags in any order
;   2. Parser detects interface has abstract flag (no missing abstract warning)
;   3. Parser detects all mutually exclusive flags regardless of order
;   4. Extra whitespace between flags is handled correctly
;   5. Bytecode is still generated (warning, not error)

.class  final abstract   super  interface   enum    module EmptyClass
.super java/lang/Object

.class_end
